Sorting on results exported to Excel never works due to the merged cells at the bottom and top headers.  These are unnecessary and should be removed.

When JIRA is upgrading old data, it first auto-exports the existing data, and you get the following log:
{noformat}
2008-10-07 18:52:49,337 main INFO [atlassian.jira.upgrade.UpgradeManagerImpl] Detected that an upgrade is needed; existing data at build 262
2008-10-07 18:52:49,349 main INFO [atlassian.jira.upgrade.UpgradeManagerImpl] Exporting the existing data..
{noformat}
We should log the full path to the export file in this case, and any other auto-exports.
eg:
{noformat}
Exporting the existing data to '/opt/Atlassian/jira/exports/autodump.xml' ...
{noformat}

*versionoperations.jsp* uses version name when constructing id for the link, e.g. {noformat}<a id="archive_<webwork:property value="name" />" ...{noformat}

The problem is that version name can contain characters that are not [valid in HTML|http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/types.html#type-name].

{quote}ID and NAME tokens must begin with a letter ([A-Za-z]) and may be followed by any number of letters, digits ([0-9]), hyphens ("-"), underscores ("_"), colons (":"), and periods (".").{quote}

{panel:title=Status|borderStyle=solid}
If you find a mixed content warning, can you create another issue describing your problem and your version of IE. Adding a comment and re-opening this issue will not get your problem reviewed. 
{panel}

When Internet Explorer displays an issue view page over HTTPS, Internet Explorer complains that the page contains both secure and nonsecure items.  For external customers for which confidentiality and privacy is important, the appearance of this dialog unnecessarily raises their anxiety level.

AssignToLeadFunction.java has this line:

 log.warn("Automatically setting assignee to lead developer "+leadName);

This should be at debug/info level.

